9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 677, L.D. 1048, “An Act to Require
10 Certain Notice Requirements for Whistleblower Protections”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §1316, sub-§10, as repealed and replaced by PL 2023, c. 405,
14 Pt. A, §124, is amended to read:
15 10. Notice of rights required. A public utility and a competitive electricity provider
16 shall notify the public utility's and the competitive electricity provider's employees,
17 affiliated interests and utility contractors of their rights under this section. A public utility
18 and a competitive electricity provider shall send an annual notice of the rights under this
19 section, which must be written in plain English, be in at least 12-point type and be sent
20 separately from any other communication, to:
21 A. Persons at the time of the notice performing a service for wages or other
22 remuneration under a contract of hire, expressed or implied, for the public utility or
23 competitive electricity provider; and
24 B. The public utility's and the competitive electricity provider's affiliated interests and
25 utility contractors.'
26 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
27 number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment replaces the bill. It requires that a public utility and a competitive
3300 electricity provider provide an annual notice to current employees, affiliated interests and
3311 utility contractors of the rights established in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 35-A,
3322 section 1316 regarding protections for persons providing testimony or information to
3333 legislative committees, the Public Utilities Commission and the Public Advocate. The
